Appendix C: Sparse Gaussian Process Implementation

C.1 Inducing Point Selection

Inducing points X_m are selected using:

Â· Kâ€‘means clustering on observed terrain features
Â· Greedy selection based on information gain
Â· Fixed spatial grid (simplest, for initial implementation)

C.2 Online Update Algorithm

1. Receive new observation (x, y)
2. Update inducing point set if necessary (if new point is informationâ€‘rich)
3. Update hyperparameters via marginal likelihood optimization every N steps
4. Maintain inducing outputs u and covariance Î£

C.3 Complexity Analysis

Â· Standard GP: O(NÂ³) â†’ intractable for N > 1000
Â· Sparse GP with M inducing points: O(NMÂ²)
Â· With M = 50, N = 1000: ~2.5M operations vs. 1B operations â†’ 400Ã— speedup

C.4 Prediction Pipeline

For a query point x*:

1. Compute kernel vector k_*m between x* and inducing points
2. Compute predictive mean: Î¼_ = k_*m K_mmâ»Â¹ u*
3. Compute predictive variance: Ïƒ_*Â² (provides uncertainty for risk assessment)

